_refine.details                                  
;In molecule A, the density between residues 53-64 is very poor. The occupancy of these atoms has been set to zero.  
In Molecule B, the density for the main chain was clearly visible in OMIT maps, however, the density is weak and no side chain density could be identified. After several trials of refinement, the occupancy has been set to 0.6 for atoms of residues 53-64.  
Also, the final amino acids Asn174 and Leu175 could not be localized in the structure.
;
